{
  "stem": "19923.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 106.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the neighboring farms used the older people's help and probably gave them in the barter system food back for whatever we needed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But that's how we survived as a group.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not ever in the danger because this was still-- this was already in the foothills of the Pyrenees Mountains.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we knew that there was trouble brewing, but we did not know at that particular time that it was an imminent danger.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Our people were making arrangements already at that time to get out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And at that particular time, Eleanor Roosevelt started the program of Save the Jews-- Save the Children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the American Quakers opened up eight offices in Europe to try and assist any Jewish child who could get parental permission to help them get to the United States as part of this Save the Children program.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my brother, Joe, still knew the whereabouts of my mother, wrote to her.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she gave written permission for us to go.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And based upon that letter that my mother wrote giving her permission, the American Quakers made the arrangements for us to travel to the United States.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And In June of 1941, Joe, Martin, and I went to Marseilles and in Marseilles the American Quakers had their organization.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And from there, after six weeks staying in Marseilles, we were given travel documents to travel by train through Spain into Lisbon, Portugal to catch a boat from Lisbon, Portugal.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were-- we were joined with children from other areas from France that also had gotten parental permission.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In my group from Chateau de la Hille, there were I'm guessing now maybe 10 or 12, not all of them, that were given parental permission to travel and were part of that group.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were the second group.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
